OpenBounty <version>
====================

OpenBounty is an open-source reimplementation of the 1990 strategy game
King's Bounty. The engine ships without game data; you must supply your
own asset pack.


INSTALL

  Linux:    extract the tarball and run ./openbounty
  Windows:  extract the zip and double-click openbounty.exe
  macOS:    extract the zip; first launch will be blocked by Gatekeeper.
            Right-click openbounty in Finder, choose Open, then click
            Open in the dialog. Or, from a terminal:
              xattr -dr com.apple.quarantine ./openbounty


ASSET PACK

  OpenBounty looks for a *.openbounty file next to the binary, or in
  your user packs directory. To create a pack from your own copy of
  the King's Bounty DOS distribution:

      ./openbounty --extract /path/to/KB.EXE

  This produces a .openbounty file you can keep next to the binary.


CONTROLS

  Movement:   Arrow keys or numpad (8 directions on numpad)
  View army:  A         View character: V         Map: M
  Spells:     U         Contract:       I         Puzzle: P
  End week:   W         Search:         S
  Save+quit:  Q         Fast quit: Ctrl+Q
  Cheat menu: F10
  Exit menu:  Esc


